(3) Suffering can be ended by overcoming ignorance and attachment. (4) The path to the suppression of suffering is the Noble Eightfold Path, which consists of right views, right intention, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right-mindedness, and right contemplation. only to find an e-mail from Mike (my b/f) on myspace. Well, I read it figuring it's just more of that "I miss you" stuff. Apparently a girl named Britney that he's friends with works for Off the Hook Corp. which has a lot to do with the tv show Viva La Bam on Mtv. Well, she called him yesterday and invited him to a taping of the show for the upcoming 4th season and told him to bring a of couple friends. Since I am his girlfriend I was the first person he asked. Of course I said yes. So, in about 3 weeks I get to go get drunk, party it up, and do a lot of crazy shit with Bam Margera, the boys of CKY, and the Bloodhound Gang and it's all going to be taped and aired on Mtv. This is not going to end well, but it will be fun while it lasts. So, I am so fucking excited right now it's not even funny. I get to hang out with Bam fucking Margera, CKY, and the fucking Bloodhound Gang!!!!! On top of it...all expenses are going to be paid for by Off the Hook Corp. and when it's all over we get a shit load of free dvds, cds, clothes, etc. I was so excited I didn't fall asleep until about 5 or 6 AM. I think I'm more excited about this than the Trio concert I'm going to the weekend before the Bam taping. My life fucking rules! I know you're jealous. lol ^_-
